-- Hungary Stocks: Refiner Mol, OTP Bank Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-21T16:19:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/hungary-stocks-refiner-mol-otp-bank-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
dropped 0.9 percent to 19,053.07 as of the close in Budapest.
The following are among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL) , Hungary’s largest refiner, dropped the most in
more than a month on concern the government will face delays in
international bailout talks. The shares fell 2.3 percent to
19,200 forint, the steepest decline since Feb. 10.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell 1.5
percent to 3,891 forint. The bank had its recommendation cut to
underweight from equalweight at Morgan Stanley, which reduced
its price target for the stock by 16 percent to 3,600 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
